title: Elephantmen Pack (Image|2006->|Dgtl|Empire+Novus) (data9724)
description:
This is not a new torrent but merely a re-post of a pack uploaded at KAT by <a href=" http://thepiratebay.se/user/data9724/" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://thepiratebay.se/user/data9724/</a>  on 1 September. Grand total of 60 scans of 58 issues:

Special issue "Pilot" (multiple scans):
   Elephantmen 9.5 (2007) (Digital) (JK-Empire)
   Elephantmen - The Pilot (Image) (2007) (Empire-Adventurers) (2560)
Issues 0-50:
   Elephantmen   4.5 (2006)      (Digital) (Godfathers-Empire)
   Elephantmen  1- 6 (2006-2007) (Digital) (Godfathers-Empire)
   Elephantmen  7-33 (2007-2011) (Digital) (JK-Empire)
   Elephantmen 34    (2011)      (webrip-TheGroup)
   Elephantmen 35    (2011)      (webrip-Empire)
   Elephantmen 36-42 (2011-2012) (digital-Empire)
   Elephantmen 43    (2012)      (Tarutaru-DCP-HD)
   Elephantmen 44-50 (2012-2013) (Novus-HD)
Miniseries + special issue "War Toys":
   Elephantmen - War Toys 1-3 (2007-2008) (Digital) (JK-Empire)
   Elephantmen - War Toys - Yvette (2009) (Image) (c2c) (neverwhere-DCP)   [renamed]
Special issue "Man & Elephantman" (multiple scans):
   Elephantmen 30.5 (2011) (Digital) (JK-Empire)
   Elephantmen - Man & Elephantman 001 (c2c) (2011) (Archangel-CPS)
Artbook issue:   Elephantmen - Cover Stories 01 (2011) (Minutemen-DarthSax)

As regards quality, this collection is arguably perfect. I might have chosen Minutemen's traditional versions over the lo-res webrips for 34-35, and the Empire releases over the Novus ones for the latest issues - but then again, I might not.
